# HTTP Basics

## Definition
HTTP (HyperText Transfer Protocol) is used for communication between client and server.

## Why it matters
All APIs and integrations use HTTP to send and receive data.

## Real Example
When you open a website:
Browser sends request → Server sends response

## Key Points
- Stateless protocol
- Request/Response model
- Common methods:
  - GET → Read data
  - POST → Create data
  - PUT → Update data
  - DELETE → Remove data

##HTTPS status codes 
200--Ok success 
201--created and new record made 
400--Bad request (client side problem)
401--wrong password (Authentation failed)
500--Server error 
